##  Purpose

Our client is lookng to engage a Business Analyst on an initial 6 month
contract with the probability of extensions. This role will provide business
analysis expertise within the Application Modernisation Program. The role sits
within the Product and Change team who provide the upstream analysis and scope
of development priorities.

##  Responsibilities

  * Lead business analysis activities within the Falco project to deliver the business requirements and business process, governance design and documentation in support of quarterly planning commitments and the product roadmap. 
  * Support the execution of the Falco Roadmap by providing business analysis expertise in accordance with the project methodology and upstream project ways of working through user story and ticket creation and refinement. 
  * Liaise directly with business users and stakeholders to define clear requirements and scope. Support the Subject Matter Expert and Product Owner to document the requirements that will be used to scope and estimate the effort required and determine the deliverables. 
  * Critically assess current state documentation and input into future state process design. 
  * Maintain a strong connection between the product and the project teams, to ensure expectations are both managed and met. 
  * Assist stakeholders in facilitating UAT activities, including the creation of test cases/scenarios and triaging of defects/bugs. Assist where required. 
  * Assist during releases and facilitate hand over to support as needed. 
  * Work independently or as a part of a group delivery as required. 

This is not an exhaustive list of position responsibilities. Specific duties
may vary over time.

##  Skills and qualifications

  * Experience working in IT streams in a BA capacity, including in development/ agile teams. 
  * High level of analytical, research and problem-solving skills to provide value adding solutions and recommendations. 
  * High level of business engagement, change management, training, and communications skills. 
  * Excellent communication skills, showing ability to work directly with system owners to clarify requirements and translate this into practical solutions. 
  * Experience in the planning and execution of testing and UAT. 
  * Excellent problem solving and analytical skills, able to listen and ask the right questions to ensure the right information. 
  * Able to work well within a cross-functional team of professionals, including working autonomously and collaboratively as the circumstances require. 

